Awesome variety with a focus on healthier consumables. Prices feel fair and even generous for the proportions. I walk in for smoothies all the time. One thing the pops into my head could be improved is the decor and quality of interiors. Overall I enjoy what they have going on.
I’m disappointed at this place. I ordered a bacon egg and cheese on a everything bagel. The bacon just tasted like oil, and it looked old. Nothing fresh about this sandwich.
amazing sandwiches. cool staff. also amazing vegen baker . cookies are 10/10.
Impressive sandwich & smoothie selection, vegan, gluten free!! Friendly staff , great for pick up.
I order from here for myself and for my staff at work and they are always quick and never make any mistakes.
Great dairy free vegetarian options.

I ordered food for my son and wife through my wife's seamless account.  Not only they were late but most dangerous thing that happened was that I found small plastic shards in both order of fries one was meant for my 2 year old son thank goodness I checked and suffered a piece stuck in my throat for a day luckily my wife took it out with tweezers.  Thank you for the refund even though the counter lady answered with  a Nonchalant  attitude if my son ate those fries god forbid we would have bigger issues Tell the cook  to use mesh lids not stab carelessly through with a knife.  The perfect word...  DANGEROUS ...
Decent food, though horrified by the amount of waste packaging for a eat in. Completely unnecessary.
The food was amazing and affordable, but the server forgot to put in my food and I waited over 20 min for a veggie burger.

I’ve ordered from here twice and was really happy; they do excellent vegan and vegetarian options! I love the Vegan Tex Mex Burrito. The blended juices are great, the cake I got was pretty good but not stellar, the cappuccino fared better and arrived hot and completely protected from spillage. This is my go-to now for a coffee delivery and a vegan breakfast when I’m not trying to spend too much, I WISH this place was right next to me instead of a mile away!

Great food both vegan and not vegan . It's a small place not a lot of seating but great variety the only reason I didnt give it 5 stars is because they can be a bit unorganized which makes sense since their menu is so big .
they forgot a few things from my order but they sent it all again, the food was very good, Liz was super helpful and kind

Ordered Vegan Tex Mex buritto and was given a guac burrito (eggs and cheese). Instead of apologizing (despite me not being hostile and was just giving a heads up incase of miscommunication between order and cook) they insisted I ordered a non vegan burrito. Never going back.
7 of us, (vegans and meaties) were able to eat awesome food to our heart's content. Clean, awesome music, and omg the whoopie pies ❤❤❤
Been coming here for years. Love the vegan menu!
Good food
sells a lot of healthy munchies like granola bars and hemp seeds but the real snack is the Filipino girl who works at the counter

I was looking for a breakfast place in the neighborhood and this turned out to be a great spot. They offer so many healthy and regular breakfast options, plus juices and smoothies, coffee and alternative milk options. The staff is warm and helpful. There is also room to sit down and work.
The vegan sandwiches and desserts are well done. Just a good neighborhood deli. Staff is super warm. You want to hang out there.
Lots of GF options, delicious juices at reasonable prices!

Got the order completely wrong, despite the clerk asking me to repeat myself. She even recited the order back to me. Bagel was baby sized with two tiny slices of lox. The breakfast burrito was missing eggs. For the price they charge, I would have expected better.

Although the vegan French Dip I ate was really tasty and well made, the rest of the experience was undesirable. First two items I ordered were not available. As in, I didn't know until after I paid. I had to ask for my Americano, twice, and the coffee was not good coffee. Not even if it was at a gas station. With completely terrible service I gave three stars, because it was truly a tasty sandwhich of a veganized favorite.

My 1st time here was horrible. They made my sandwich entirely too fast to the point where you just know something is wrong with it. When I got my sandwich I really wasn’t what I wanted. Their menu is crammed together. My smoothie is not a smoothie smh. If you’re black don’t come here! Just being honest. At least the cashier was friendly
Great place if you're vegan and want a vegan sandwich or dessert. Even if youre not vegan it's a great place to eat, drink, and chill for a bit.
Get the smoothies.
Great coffee! Bagels are pretty good.
Awesome options for vegans! Premade meals and dessert and you can get tons of sandwiches and meals made on the spot as well!

Ive been ordering from here for 2 years now so I've had quite a lot of experience with them. Their delivery time is always around an hour (which is what was estimated so thats decent, I guess) but my biggest gripe is the food they have is always so bland and dry. I've never had a meal that was truly delicious, it was just something to fill my stomach with at work. Overall a so-so experience, but I can't recommend the food to anyone.

Vegan refrigerated pasta options  are really dry. For the price & portion they should at least be a little more generous with the sauce. Deli Mac has an overwhelming taste of olives, very little tofu, dry as hell, lacking a balance of flavors. No bueno The pesto pasta tastes good, balanced pesto flavor but still so so dry. Also, is young woman with long hair at counter an Actor? She sounded like she was trying way too hard to be polite and it was coming off very insincere :(
The best I ever had
Great food but service can be dicey. Ordering process takes much longer than normal and phones are down half the time.

Absolutely the best potato salad anywhere, and their seitan french dip sandwich is still one of my absolute favourites. Also highly recommend the spicy quinoa salad and cashew pesto pasta salad.  Yes -- their prices are a bit high, but to me it's worth every penny knowing I'm getting a freshly-made, quality product.
Good for vegan options.
Excellent restaurant,  not that fancy one, but they provide a nice, fresh food. From breakfast,  vegan lunch and dinner, fresh smothies and lovely vegan cokies. And the delivery always on time.

Excellent!  There's something for everyone on this menu...there are healthy options, vegan options for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Since I am vegan, I chose the falafel burger on a homemade multigrain roll/vegan cheese and sweet potato fries for dinner. I quenched my thirst with unsweetened yerba mate tea. The staff was friendly and wait time was only 10 minutes!

I live somewhat close to this place and every Saturday that I have been there I feel that I am annoying the women that work there. They always seem to be upset that I am ordering just coffee. I thought it was just me but I went in again with my mother hoping I would have a different experience but my mom actually called the girl out of her attitude not knowing I feel the same way everytime I order. I by the way only order coffee never had the food. And the coffee isnt that great. Now I just walk up to Dunkin’ Donuts for a cup of joe in the morning. Was trying to help a local business stay in business but that nasty employees are what drove me away.
I love the food but they never answer the phone and their online ordering is always down. Sorry guys you lose my business almost every time. Wake up!!! Answer your phone

After speaking to the manger about my previous altercation with the worker Meagan he shocked me saying he saw my first review and talked to her I said I appreciate that and even more that he actually reads the reviews. He then apologized for Meagan behavior and even gave me the tacos I originally came in there to get the staff was so nice and concerned and well the tacos you can see the picture they are so good the picture isn't doing what my taste buds are tasting and thats heaven great food will be back

This entire place was sniffing it's own ass when I showed up at 9am for some breakfast. Artisan coffee that was just a badly made americano, a breakfast burrito that the waitress made seem like an end of the world chore to actually order off the guy who had to cook it, and God forbid you want to add some orange juice to your order because the hip might fall out of her stir if she actually had to work for a while.  And yes, before you ask I got the wrong group order with only 3 people in the entire place. Wilco will never eat here.

Like melt in your mouth, incredible freshness-- AMAZING customer service. I've ordered and gone in person. This place is fantastic. AND, the prices are reasonable.
